.TH "clockevents_config_and_register" 9 "clockevents_config_and_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
clockevents_config_and_register \- Configure and register a clock event device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" clockevents_config_and_register
.BI "(struct clock_event_device *dev "  ","
.BI "u32 freq "  ","
.BI "unsigned long min_delta "  ","
.BI "unsigned long max_delta "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device to register
.IP "freq" 12
The clock frequency
.IP "min_delta" 12
The minimum clock ticks to program in oneshot mode
.IP "max_delta" 12
The maximum clock ticks to program in oneshot mode
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
min/max_delta can be 0 for devices which do not support oneshot mode.
